```julia
function clean_column(col)
    return Symbol(lowercase(strip(col, whitespace), replace(col, [" ", "-"] => "_"))
end
```

This function uses `Symbol` to ensure the resulting string is a valid Julia identifier. It first strips leading and trailing whitespaces using `strip(col, whitespace)`, then lowercases the string with `lowercase(col)`. Finally, it replaces spaces and hyphens with underscores using `replace(col, [" ", "-"] => "_")` to create a clean column name.
